headline: LKQ Q3 Deep Dive: Portfolio Simplification and Cost Controls Stand Out Amidst Macroeconomic Headwinds
summary: Automotive parts company LKQ (NASDAQ:LKQ) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025 as sales only rose 1.3% year on year to $3.50 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.84 per share was 11% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
